            <scopecontent id="aspace_a0a9218531162e21ec87e8992c7650e4">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The Truman Seymour Papers consist of six sketchbooks and notebooks. Most of the sketches are pencil drawings, although there are also some watercolors. The drawings are either generally copies of the old masters or sketches of Italian scenes. The papers were donated to Yale University by Irene Weir in 1935. The Truman Seymour sketchbooks originally belonged to Robert W. Weir, professor of drawing at the United States Military Academy and father-in-law of Seymour.</p>
               <p>For additional Truman Seymour material, see the John Ferguson Weir Papers (MS 550). The Weir Papers contain eight Truman Seymour letters.</p>
            </scopecontent>
